PSWSSearchRequest

public PSWSSearchRequest(PSWSSearchParams searchParams)
Create a standard search request.

Parameters:

PSWSSearchRequest

public PSWSSearchRequest(String searchName,
                         Map params)
Create an internal search request.

Parameters:
searchName - The name of an internal search, may not be null or empty. Used as the name of the request page to make a request to the internal search application.
params - Parameters to pass with the request to the internal search application. May be null. Key is the parameter name and value is the parameter value, both as String objects. A shallow copy of the map is stored in this object.

setCaseInsensitiveSearch

public void setCaseInsensitiveSearch(boolean caseInsensitive)
Determines if a case-insensitive search is to be performed.

Parameters:
caseInsensitive - true to perform a case-insensitive search, false to use the database default. If the database is case-insensitive by default, then setting this value will have no effect.
